SomniaAgentConsumer::sendRequest
├── when msg.value is less than the platform deposit floor
│   └── it should revert with InsufficientDeposit.
└── when msg.value is greater than or equal to the platform deposit floor
    ├── it should forward the full msg.value to createRequest.
    ├── it should mark the request id pending.
    └── it should emit AgentRequested with the request id and the agent id.

# DEPOSIT SEMANTICS (corrected 2026-06-01 from live research + CLAUDE.md non-negotiable).
# getRequestDeposit() is an operations-reserve FLOOR (= minPerAgentDeposit * subSize), NOT the
# execution cost. Forwarding only the floor leaves perAgentBudget = 0 -> runners skip -> TimedOut.
# CLAUDE.md requires msg.value >= minPerAgentDeposit*subSize + p_i*subSize, so the caller over-funds
# and the consumer forwards the WHOLE msg.value; unused budget is rebated to the contract via receive().
# There is therefore NO refund path (the prior "refund the excess" subtree is removed — it also
# eliminated the call/transfer reentrancy footgun). msg.value below the floor still reverts.
